The paper deals with channel state feedback schemes for a MIMO-OFDM broadcast channel, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the comparison of achievable rates under different feedback schemes, which falls under signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM).
